Foxfingers flew across what will one day be Europe, passing many 
different animals, plants, and even prehumans but none seemed to have 
the DNA sequence his master was looking for. he saw the skeleton of a 
large tiger, the shiny teeth caught his interest so one by one he 
plucked them out. "While I'm here I might as well add something to my 
collection." After pulling teeth he hopped aboard his hoverboard and 
continued south towards the Cybertronian Fire.

--- In nbwrpg@egroups.com, "CYBERWOLF4" <cyberwolf4@p...> wrote:
> The three arrivals got situated and began thier planning.
> 
> The old bot stood up adressing the other two. "I want the two of 
you to
> start searching this planet for the dominant DNA we need, 
Foxfingers go out
> and search this sorry excuse for a planet. keep me advised of your
> progress." He turned his head toward the other bot, "My daughter, 
you will
> begin setting up my lab, when Foxfingers returns we will need to 
begin
> quickly." He turned back to the red and brown bot he'd adressed 
first. "And
> Foxfingers, try to stay out of trouble this time."
> 
> With a quick glance and a sly smile the bot known as Foxfingers 
exited the
> ship. "I'll return my lord, with everything you need." He lowered a
> hoverboard to his feet and began his journey south. "I'll begin 
with the
> larger concentration of Maximals and work my way back from there."
> 
> His journey to what will one day be Africa had begun, he hoped for 
an
> uneventful voyage but kept his gaurd up just in case.
